article.description: Christine Hyde scored 18 points to lead Texas Tech (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) to a 70-64 win over Illinois on Saturday.
article.headline: Christine Hyde, Texas Tech hold off Illinois
article.linkText: Hyde scores 18, leads Texas Tech past Illinois
article.story:
CHICAGO -- Christine Hyde scored 18 points to lead Texas Tech (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) to a 70-64 win over Illinois on Saturday.

The Lady Raiders made 25 of 35 free throws to hang on against Illinois (4-6). Karisma Penn scored 12 points and Alex Burke had 11 for the Illini.

The Lady Raiders forced 18 turnovers Texas Tech (9-0)  is ranked the highest in the AP poll since they opened the 2005 season at No. 13 and fell to No. 14 on Nov. 21, 2005.
